[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip sources' to see which modules have tip files available
[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip list --from MODULE' to browse tips from a specific module
[SDG-TIPS]: Exclude noisy modules by running 'sdgtip config exclude add MODULE'
[SDG-TIPS]: Each module can ship its own tips under ~/.local/tips/MODULE/tips.list
[SDG-TIPS]: The sdgtip CLI aggregates tips from all installed modules automatically
[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip random' to get a random tip on demand
[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip list' to browse and search all tips interactively with fzf
[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip --from MODULE' to focus tips on a specific module
[SDG-TIPS]: Use 'sdgtip config exclude add MODULE' to silence a noisy module
